%md
Return all of the data by using the `collect` function. Take note of the type of the return value;
in Python it will be a list of strings, and in Scala it will be an array of strings.

%pyspark

sc.setJobGroup("Working with RDDs","Display the contents of the makes1RDD")
for make in makes1RDD.collect(): print(make)

%pyspark

sc.setJobGroup("Working with RDDs","Display the contents of the allMakesRDD")
for make in allMakesRDD.collect(): print(make)

%pyspark

sc.setJobGroup("Working with RDDs","Display the unique makes")
for make in allMakesRDD.distinct().collect(): print(make)
